          "merged_at": null
        },
        "body": "## Summary\r\nAdds comprehensive framework integration documentation to help developers integrate Gardevoir/reseter.css into modern JavaScript frameworks.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n-  New `docs/frameworks.md` with integration patterns for React, Next.js, Vue, Nuxt, Angular, Svelte\r\n-  Added build tool examples (Vite, Webpack, Rollup, Parcel)\r\n-  Performance optimization guidelines (preload, CDN, bundle size)\r\n-  Troubleshooting section for common integration issues\r\n-  Updated `README.md` with link to framework guide\r\n\r\n## Frameworks Covered\r\n- React (Vite & CRA)\r\n- Next.js (App Router & Pages Router)\r\n- Vue 3 (Vite & CLI)\r\n- Nuxt 3\r\n- Angular\r\n- Svelte/SvelteKit\r\n\r\nFixes #364\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Added a Framework Integration guide with framework/build-tool patterns, SSR and performance tips, troubleshooting, and a quick-reference cheat sheet; updated the README comparison table for clearer presentation and values.\n* **New Features**\n  * Added a self-contained React + Vite example demonstrating correct import order, global vs component styling, interactive demos, usage instructions, and project scripts.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
